obo:GO_0098982  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4779  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6: \"live-cell labeling of MSNs cotransfected with HA-tagged CACNA2D subunits and soluble\neGFP revealed that all CACNA2D isoforms are expressed on the surface of presynaptic axonal varicosities and thus can in theory contribute to synaptic functions in GABAergic neurons\"\n\nFigure 8: presynaptic overexpression of CACNA2D3 (α2δ-3 Calcium Channel) was enriched at synaptic puncta\n\nDavies A, et al. 2010 (PMID:20080692, Fig. 4G) showed CACNA2D subunits are most likely linked to the plasma membrane via GPI anchor, hence we selected \"anchored component of ... membrane\". Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Animal procedures for WT BALB/c and 2 mutant mice were performed\"\n\n\"The α2δ-3 knock-out mice (α2δ-3-/-) generated by Deltagen (B6.129P2-Cacna2d3tm1Dgen; Neely et al., 2010) were originally purchased from The Jackson Laboratory and provided by Jutta Engel (Saarland University, Germany). Knock-out was obtained by targeted insertion of a bacterial LacZ cassette into the Cacna2d3 gene such that the endogenous promoter drives the expression of β-galactosidase. The following primers were used for detecting the WT allele (F1-R, 183 bp fragment) and the knock-out allele (F2-R, 331 bp fragment): F1: 5'-TAGAAAAGATGCACTGGTCACCAGG-3', F2: 5'-GGGCCAGCTCATTCCTCCCACTCAT-3', R: 5'-GCAGAAGGCACATTGCCATACTCAC-3' by use of standard PCR conditions (annealing at 63°C for 30 s).\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099029 replaced by GO:0048787" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4779" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

